pullRequest.body:
The first of 2 PRs refactoring group cohomology to use the bar resolution. Given a comm ring `k` and a group `G`, the bar resolution is the projective resolution of `k` as a trivial `G`-representation whose `n`th object is `G‚Åø ‚Üí‚ÇÄ k[G]`, with representation defined pointwise by the left regular representation on k[G], and whose differentials send `(g‚ÇÄ, ..., g‚Çô)` to `g‚ÇÄ¬∑(g‚ÇÅ, ..., g‚Çô) + ‚àë (-1) ≤‚Å∫¬π¬∑(g‚ÇÄ, ..., g‚±ºg‚±º‚Çä‚ÇÅ, ..., g‚Çô) + (-1)‚Åø‚Å∫¬π¬∑(g‚ÇÄ, ..., g‚Çô‚Çã‚ÇÅ)` for `j = 0, ... , n - 1`.
The refactor means we can reuse this material to set up group homology. 

This PR defines an isomorphism between the objects in the standard resolution and the bar resolution, i.e. an isomorphism of representations `k[G‚Åø‚Å∫¬π] ‚âÖ (G‚Åø ‚Üí‚ÇÄ k[G])`, called `Rep.diagonalSuccIsoFree`.

Moves:
- groupCohomology.resolution.actionDiagonalSucc -> Action.diagonalSuccIsoTensorTrivial
- groupCohomology.resolution.diagonalSucc -> Rep.diagonalSuccIsoTensorTrivial

---
